ring`, and required resources, and says both `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.glassfish:jakarta.el:4.0.0 --stacktrace` and `runNativeTraceImage` passed. That matches the later successful runs in `human-intervention-logs/org.glassfish:jakarta.el:4.0.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-20T12-44-54-350870Z.log` and `human-intervention-logs/org.glassfish:jakarta.el:4.0.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-20T12-45-08-960247Z.log`.\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Check out the preserved branch and review the generated tests plus `metadata/org.glassfish/jakarta.el/4.0.0/reachability-metadata.json`.\\n2. Re-run the library verification with the expected GraalVM toolchain, especially `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.glassfish:jakarta.el:4.0.0 --stacktrace`, and confirm the preserved fix still passes.\\n3. If it passes, promote the preserved changes; if `generateMetadata` still fails, fix the local `native-image-agent` setup first and then rerun the metadata-generation / native-trace steps.\"}}\n{\"type\":\"turn.completed\",\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":236574,\"cached_input_tokens\":182016,\"output_tokens\":5580,\"reasoning_output_tokens\":2359}}\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
