{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_37","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job failed for `org.glassfish:jakarta.el:4.0.0`.\n\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-1519-library-new-request-org.glassfish-jakarta.el-4.0.0-43f6ff63\n\nThe most likely failing stage was the metadata-generation / repair loop after test generation. The generated tests are present and the dynamic-access report reached 12/13 covered calls (92.31%), but `logs/org.glassfish:jakarta.el:4.0.0/native-test-verify/cycle-0-generateMetadata-2026-06-07T21-09-40-999380Z.log` shows `:generateMetadata` failing because the JVM could not load `native-image-agent` (`Could not find agent library native-image-agent ... libnative-image-agent.so`). Before that, `logs/org.glassfish:jakarta.el:4.0.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-07T21-08-55-820047Z.log` shows the native tests failing on concrete missing metadata paths: `InvalidClassException: com.sun.el.lang.FunctionMapperImpl; no valid constructor`, `Provider com.sun.el.ExpressionFactoryImpl not found` / `ClassNotFoundException`, and missing bundle `com.sun.el.Messages`. `logs/org.glassfish:jakarta.el:4.0.0/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-06-07T21-09-42-067662Z.log` narrows this to `MissingSerializationRegistrationError: Cannot serialize or deserialize 'com.sun.el.lang.FunctionMapperImpl'`.\n\nThere is also evidence that the preserved branch contains a viable fix: `logs/org.glassfish:jakarta.el:4.0.0/metadata-fix/codex.log` records added metadata for `FunctionMapperImpl` serialization plus `ExpressionFactoryImpl` / `com.sun.el.Messages`, and later verification logs `logs/org.glassfish:jakarta.el:4.0.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-07T21-16-04-475468Z.log`, `...21-16-28-305816Z.log`, and `...21-16-50-481142Z.log` all end with 6/6 native tests passing. However, `stats/org.glassfish/jakarta.el/4.0.0/execution-metrics.json` still marks the run as `failure` with no promoted test/metadata artifacts.\n\nNext steps:\n1. Check out the preserved branch and review `tests/src/org.glassfish/jakarta.el/4.0.0` plus `metadata/org.glassfish/jakarta.el/4.0.0/reachability-metadata.json`.\n2. Re-run `./gradlew generateMetadata -Pcoordinates=org.glassfish:jakarta.el:4.0.0` with a GraalVM installation that has `libnative-image-agent.so` available on the expected library path.\n3. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.glassfish:jakarta.el:4.0.0`; if it stays green, promote the preserved metadata/tests instead of regenerating from scratch."}}
